TWO burnt bodies, with three dead cows near them, were discovered by a resident at a dumping site in Casteel near Bushbuckridge, Mpumalanga, on Monday, 9 January. Provincial commissioner Lieutenant-General Semakaleng Manamela has condemned the senseless killings. Colonel Donald Mdhluli said a resident alerted cops to the gruesome discovery. “Alongside the deceased were three carcasses of cows. The police are in a process of finding their families so the two can be identified. The motive behind the killing is unknown, and a postmortem will be conducted to determine the cause of death,” he said. You must be SIGNED IN to read comments Mdhluli said cops had since launched an investigation to include finding the owner/s of the cattle. Anyone with information can contact Detective Lieutenant-Colonel Aaron Digoro on 082 318 9925 or CrimeStop on 08600 10111.